  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="2"/>
   <head>Precepts for Seruingmen.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>WHO dwelles in place where Enuie raines,</l>
      <l>and spendes his life in clubbish soyle,</l>
      <l>Shall reape but heapes of endlesse paines,</l>
      <l>and put his life to wearie toyle.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Who so beleeueth tattling tales,</l>
      <l>Proceeding out of euery pate,</l>
      <l>The fort of Enuie surely scales,</l>
      <l>and yeldes him selfe to froward fate.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Who heareth much and medleth least,</l>
      <l>shall scape the sling of chiding chaps:</l>
      <l>Who seekes to liue at quiet rest,</l>
      <l>must be content what euer haps.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
